S�ren Vejrup Carlsen wrote:

&gt; Dear All.
&gt; When I start heritrix-0.7.1 (as of April 23,2004), I get the message the
&gt; heritrix_out.log:
&gt; EVENT  The scratchDir you specified:
&gt; /home/heritrix/heritrix-0.7.1/jsp-compiled is unusable.
&gt;
&gt; Maybe, it&#39;s just something to ignore, but what does it mean?

If the webpages still work (and they do for me despite this message) you 
can safely ignore this
message. The scratch dir is set in a file to specify a directory to 
write the JSP compiled pages
when we are running development versions. Without it they would be 
rebuilt between restarts.

Since our builds now come with the JSP pages prebuilt and bundled inside 
WAR files there is
of course no need for this directive and our build should really drop 
the file that specifies it
(...webapps/admin/WEB-INF/jetty-web.xml).

But as I said before, it shouldn&#39;t damage anything.

- Kris

